description: Start of n consecutive integers with distinct number of divisors.
links: C. Rivera, The Prime Problems and Puzzles Connection - see Problem 20c.
example: The 5th number of this sequence, 45, means that 45, 46, 47, 48 and 49 all have distinct number of divisors: 6, 4, 2, 10 and 3, respectively
author: _Carlos Rivera_
